define({"topics":[{"title":"Chatting with meeting participants","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, the chat feature is enabled. You can communicate with all meeting     participants using the chat function. Guest users can only access the chat room through the     active meeting. <\/p>","href":"chat_others.html","attributes":{"data-id":"chat_others"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"chat_others-d459e395","topics":[]},{"title":"Raising hands","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, all meeting participants have access to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Raise       hand<\/span> feature. Toggling the hand is visible to all meeting participants. As a guest     or authenticated user, you can raise and lower hands throughout the meeting to request to speak,     answer a poll, or as a form of silent acknowledgment. Moderators can lower a userâ€™s hand. <img class=\"image\" src=\"Images\/raise_hands.png\"\/><\/p>","href":"raise_hand.html","attributes":{"data-id":"raise_hands"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"raise_hands-d459e414","topics":[]},{"title":"Muting and unmuting my audio","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Meeting participants can mute (<img class=\"image\" src=\"Images\/mute.jpg\"\/>)     and unmute (<img class=\"image\" src=\"Images\/unmute.png\"\/>) their microphones on     demand. Sametime notifies users when background noise is detected and when users speak while     being muted. When needed, moderators can disable the participants' microphones at any time     without notification. Most devices have a dedicated mute button that is controlled separately.     When using Sametime, users can utilize the web app microphone settings.<\/p>","href":"mute_unmute.html","attributes":{"data-id":"mute_unmute"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"mute_unmute-d459e437","topics":[]},{"title":"Enabling and disabling my camera","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">All users can enable or disable their camera in a meeting. To lower bandwidth usage or     to avoid distractions during a meeting, moderators can turn off active cameras. The video stream     of users will be limited to the last few speakers. All other videos with their microphone are     inactive or muted. <\/p>","href":"enable_disable.html","attributes":{"data-id":"enable_disable"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"enable_disable-d459e460","topics":[]},{"title":"Sharing my screen","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, you can share your screen with all meeting participants during a     meeting.<\/p>","href":"start_stop_camera.html","attributes":{"data-id":"start_stop_camera"},"menu":{"hasChildren":true},"tocID":"start_stop_camera-d459e479","next":"start_stop_camera-d459e479"},{"title":"Leaving a meeting","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can leave a meeting at any time. Leaving the meeting as a user does not                 impact the status of the meeting. Depending on moderator settings, the user can                 re-join the ongoing meeting. To leave a meeting, select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Leave<\/span>                 <img class=\"image\" src=\"Images\/leave.png\"\/>. <\/p>","href":"leave_meeting.html","attributes":{"data-id":"leave_meeting"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"leave_meeting-d459e517","topics":[]},{"title":"Choosing how participants are displayed","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The participant list <img class=\"image\" src=\"Images\/participants.png\"\/> allows you to view the meeting participants and perform     group functions.<\/p>","href":"share_screen.html","attributes":{"data-id":"share_screen"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"share_screen-d459e541","topics":[]},{"title":"Managing video quality","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">All meeting participants can change the meeting video quality from <em class=\"ph i\">audio only<\/em> to       <em class=\"ph i\">high definition<\/em> depending on the quality of your connection. You can make changes to     these settings at any time, and this only affects behavior on your meeting login.<\/p>","href":"manage_video.html","attributes":{"data-id":"manage_video"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"manage_video-d459e562","topics":[]},{"title":"Changing my background","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">To hide your physical environment, you can add a filter to blur your surroundings or         use an image to obscure your background. The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Change background<\/span>         feature is accessible from the preview window and the in-meeting menu, which means you can         modify your background before or during a meeting. Contact your administrator if this         feature is unavailable. <\/p>","href":"t_change_background.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_change_background"},"menu":{"hasChildren":true},"tocID":"t_change_background-d459e587","next":"t_change_background-d459e587"},{"title":"Sharing a video","href":"youtube_share_video.html","attributes":{"data-id":"youtube_share_video"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"youtube_share_video-d459e664","topics":[]},{"title":"Viewing the meeting in full screen","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can expand the window of the meeting to fill the entire monitor screen. <\/p>","href":"screen_size.html","attributes":{"data-id":"screen_size"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"screen_size-d459e681","topics":[]},{"title":"Copying a meeting link","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You need the meeting link or name in order to join or access the meeting. To copy the     meeting link, scroll over the bottom of the meeting window and select the three dots for the     menu. Depending on the user type and access level, the following options are displayed on the       <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Actions<\/span> menu. <\/p>","href":"copy_meeting.html","attributes":{"data-id":"copy_meeting"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"copy_meeting-d459e700","topics":[]},{"title":"Adjusting the camera and microphone settings within the meeting","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Users can make changes to their camera and microphone settings during a meeting. Scroll     over the bottom of the meeting window and select the three dots for the settings. Select       <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Settings<\/span>. Depending on the user type and access level, the following     options is displayed on the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Actions<\/span> menu. <\/p>","href":"camera_microphone.html","attributes":{"data-id":"camera_microphone"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"camera_microphone-d459e722","topics":[]}]});